This falls under the domain of HCI, which deals with the design and evaluation of interactive systems for human use. 
2. cs.CY (Computers and Society) - The paper addresses issues related to fairness and quality in crowdsourcing platforms, which have implications for the broader societal impact of technology. This aligns with the scope of cs.CY, which covers the social and ethical aspects of computing. 
3. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper discusses the role of social pressure in inflating reputation scores on crowdsourcing platforms, which is a topic relevant to the study of social networks and their effects on behavior. 
4. cs.SD (Software Engineering) - The paper proposes a new reputation system for crowdsourcing platforms, which involves the development and implementation of software. This falls under the domain of software engineering, which deals with the design, development, and maintenance of software systems.
